This wraps the Skype token provider with the caching fallback when using legacy Skype tokens.

**Additional Issue — `needFresh` Violation Logged But Not Enforced** (module 573):
```javascript
N.needFresh && H.token === I && 
  R.error("API violation: Trouter auth token provider got a request with needRefresh=true, but returned the same token as last time anyway.")
```
The code logs an error but continues with the stale token anyway.

**Impact**: In a revocation scenario (Continuous Access Evaluation / CAE), the Trouter connection could remain authenticated with a revoked token, allowing continued access to real-time messaging even after a security event requires immediate session termination.

